le an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Gwrydyr","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Gwythyr ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gwythyr","meanings":["Traditional: derived in Roman times from the Latin name <b>Victor</b> . A character with this name appears in the <i>Mabinogi</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Gwrydyr Ap Dyfnaint was born about 1070, in Wales. She had at least 9 sons with Gwrydyr Ap Dyfnaint."},"et":{"about 1070–":"umbes 1070–Surnud","1065–Male":"1065–Surnud","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1102–Male":"1102–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1090":"1090","ABT    1100":"umbes 1100","1102":"1102","about 1070":"umbes 1070","1100":"1100","1065":"1065","about 1102":"umbes 1102","about 1100":"umbes 1100","ABT    1090":"umbes 1090","1070":"1070","of Glyn Llifon,Llandwrog,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Llandwrog, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Glynllifon, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Glynllifon, Caernarfonshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1070–":"noin 1070–Kuollut","1065–Male":"1065–Kuollut","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1102–Male":"1102–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1090":"1090","ABT    1100":"noin 1100","1102":"1102","about 1070":"noin 1070","1100":"1100","1065":"1065","about 1102":"noin 1102","about 1100":"noin 1100","ABT    1090":"noin 1090","1070":"1070"